  "text": "**notion-backup: Fixed database/data_source API distinction**\n\nCritical issue: Notion API has two different concepts:- `database_id` → `/v1/databases/{id}` endpoints- `data_source_id` → `/v1/data_sources/{id}` endpoints\n\nWhen pages have `parent.type == \"data_source_id\"`, they're rows in a data source, NOT a database. Must use:\n- `client.data_sources.retrieve()` instead of `client.databases.retrieve()`\n- `client.data_sources.query()` instead of `client.databases.query()`\n\nAlso fixed null property handling in markdown converter - some Notion pages have `None` values for properties which caused \"'NoneType' object has no attribute 'get'\" errors.",
  "sections": [
    "Project Notes"
  ],
  "timestamp": 1767696883797,
